}}\n|-\n| 27\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Seamus|Byrne}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|26\u20138\n| [[Murrayfield Stadium|Murrayfield]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1953|2|28}}\n|-\n| 28\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Michel|Crauste}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| align=center|13\u20130\n| [[Stade Olympique Yves-du-Manoir|Stade Olympique de Colombes]]\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1962|2|24}}\n|-\n| 29\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Christian|Darrouy}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|24\u20135\n| [[Lansdowne Road]], Dublin\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1963|1|26}}\n|-\n| 30\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Maurice|Richards}}<sup>4</sup>\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| align=center|30\u20139\n| [[Cardiff Arms Park]], Cardiff\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1969|4|12}}\n|-\n| 31\n!scope=row| {{sortname|John|Carleton|John Carleton (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|30\u201318\n| [[Murrayfield Stadium|Murrayfield]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1980|3|15}}\n|-\n| 32\n!scope=row| {{sortname|\u00c9ric|Bonneval}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|28\u201322\n| [[Parc des Princes]], Paris\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1987|3|7}}\n|-\n| 33\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Chris|Oti}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|35\u20133\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1988|3|19}}\n|-\n| 34\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Iwan|Tukalo}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|37\u201321\n| [[Murrayfield Stadium|Murrayfield]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1989|3|4}}\n|-\n| 35\n!scope=row| {{sortname|David|Venditti}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|32\u201315\n| [[Lansdowne Road]], Dublin\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1997|1|18}}\n|-\n| 36\n!scope=row| {{sortname|\u00c9mile|Ntamack}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| align=center|33\u201334\n| [[Stade de France]], Saint-Denis\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1999|3|6}}\n|-\n| 37\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Austin|Healey}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|59\u201312\n| [[Stadio Flaminio]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2000|3|18}}\n|-\n| 38\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Brian|O'Driscoll}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| align=center|27\u201325\n| [[Stade de France]], Saint-Denis\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2000|3|19}}\n|-\n| 39\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Rob|Henderson}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|41\u201322\n| [[Stadio Flaminio]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2001|2|3}}\n|-\n| 40\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Will|Greenwood}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| align=center|44\u201315\n| [[Millennium Stadium]], Cardiff\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2001|2|3}}\n|-\n| 41\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Brian|O'Driscoll}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|43\u201322\n| [[Lansdowne Road]], Dublin\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2002|3|2}}\n|-\n| 42\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Jason|Robinson|Jason Robinson (rugby player)}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|50\u20139\n| [[Stadio Flaminio]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2004|2|15}}\n|-\n| 43\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Mark|Cueto}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|39\u20137\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2005|3|12}}\n|-\n| 44\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Jamie|Noon}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|43\u201322\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], [[London]]\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2005|3|19}}\n|-\n| 45\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Vincent|Clerc}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|26\u201321\n| [[Stade de France]], Saint-Denis\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2008|2|9}}\n|-\n| 46\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Chris|Ashton}}<sup>4</sup>\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|59\u201313\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2011|2|12}}\n|-\n| 47\n!scope=row| {{sortname|George|North}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|61\u201320\n| [[Stadio Olimpico]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2015|3|21}}\n|-\n| 48\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Jonathan|Joseph|Jonathan Joseph (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|40\u20139\n| [[Stadio Olimpico]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2016|2|14}}\n|-\n| 49\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|C. J.|Stander}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|63\u201310\n| [[Stadio Olimpico]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2017|2|11}}\n|-\n| 50\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Craig|Gilroy}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|63\u201310\n| [[Stadio Olimpico]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2017|2|11}}\n|-\n| 51\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Jonathan|Joseph|Jonathan Joseph (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|61\u201321\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2017|3|11}}\n|-\n| 52\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Blair|Kinghorn}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|33\u201320\n| [[Murrayfield Stadium|Murrayfield]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2019|2|2}}\n|-\n| 53\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Jonny|May}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| align=center|44\u20138\n| [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2019|2|10}}\n|-\n| 54\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Josh|Adams|Josh Adams (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| align=center|42\u20130\n| [[Millennium Stadium]], Cardiff\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2020|2|01}}\n|}\n\n===Drop goals===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+Six Nations Championship drop goal hat-tricks\n! scope=col|No.\n! scope=col|Player\n! scope=col|For\n! scope=col|Against\n! scope=col|Result\n! scope=col|Venue\n! scope=col|Date\n|-\n| 1\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Pierre|Albaladejo}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|23\u20136\n| [[Stade Olympique Yves-du-Manoir|Stade Olympique de Colombes]]\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1960|4|9}}\n|-\n| 2\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Jean-Patrick|Lescarboura}}\n| {{ru|FRA}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| align=center|{{sort|09|9\u20139}}\n| [[Twickenham]], London\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1985|2|2}}\n|-\n| 3\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Diego|Dom\u00ednguez|Diego Dom\u00ednguez (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|ITA}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|34\u201320\n| [[Stadio Flaminio]], Rome\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2000|2|5}}\n|-\n| 4\n!scope=row|{{sortname|Neil|Jenkins}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| align=center|28\u201328\n| [[Murrayfield Stadium|Murrayfield]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|2001|2|17}}\n|}\n\n=== Multiple hat-tricks ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+Multiple hat-tricks\n! scope=col|Player\n! scope=col|No.\n! scope=col|Years\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Ian|Smith|Ian Smith (Scottish rugby player born 1903)}}\n| align=center|3\n| [[1924 Five Nations Championship|1924]], [[1925 Five Nations Championship|1925]]\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|WAL}} {{sortname|Johnnie|Williams|Johnny Williams (rugby player 1882\u20131916)}}\n| align=center|2\n| [[1907 Home Nations Championship|1907]], [[1910 Five Nations Championship|1910]]\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|WAL}} {{sortname|Reggie|Gibbs}}\n| align=center|2\n|[[1910 Five Nations Championship|1910]], [[1911 Five Nations Championship|1911]]\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Bill|Stewart|Bill Stewart (rugby union)}}\n| align=center|2\n|[[1913 Five Nations Championship|1913]]\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|ENG}} {{sortname|Cyril|Lowe}}\n|align=center|2\n|[[1914 Five Nations Championship|1914]]\n|-\n!scope=row|[[File:IRFU flag.svg|20px]] {{sortname|Brian|O'Driscoll}}\n|align=center|2\n|[[2000 Six Nations Championship|2000]], [[2002 Six Nations Championship|2002]]\n|-\n!scope=row|{{flagicon|ENG}} {{sortname|Jonathan|Joseph|Jonathan Joseph (rugby union)}}\n|align=center|2\n|[[2016 Six Nations Championship|2016]], [[2017 Six Nations Championship|2017]]\n|}\n\n=== Player hat-tricks by their national team ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+Player's hat-tricks by their national team\n! scope=col|Team\n! scope=col|Tries for\n! scope=col|Tries against\n! scope=col|Drop goals for\n! scope=col|Drop goals against\n! scope=col|Total for\n! scope=col|Total against\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|ENG}}\n|align=center|18\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|'''18'''\n|align=center|'''5'''\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|SCO}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|WAL}}\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|8\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|align=center|'''8'''\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|IRE}}\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|'''9'''\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|FRA}}\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|'''8'''\n|align=center|'''12'''\n|-\n!scope=row|{{ru|ITA}}\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|0\n|align=center|'''1'''\n|align=center|'''11'''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Rugby World Cup hat-tricks]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{cite book|last1=Smith |first1=David |last2=Williams |first2=Gareth |title=Fields of Praise: The Official History of The Welsh Rugby Union |year=1980 |publisher=University of Wales Press |location=Cardiff |isbn=0-7083-0766-3| ref = harv}}\n\n== References ==\n'''General'''\n* {{cite web|url=http://stats.espnscrum.com/statsguru/rugby/stats/index.html?class=1;filter=advanced;orderby=date;size=200;template=results;triesmin1=3;triesval1=tries;trophy=2;type=player;view=match|title=Six Nations \u2013 Most tries scored|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=6 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716032158/http://stats.espnscrum.com/statsguru/rugby/stats/index.html?class=1%3Bfilter%3Dadvanced%3Borderby%3Ddate%3Bsize%3D200%3Btemplate%3Dresults%3Btriesmin1%3D3%3Btriesval1%3Dtries%3Btrophy%3D2%3Btype%3Dplayer%3Bview%3Dmatch|archivedate=16 July 2014}}\n* {{cite news |url=http://stats.espnscrum.com/statsguru/rugby/stats/index.html?class=1;filter=advanced;orderby=drop_goals;template=results;trophy=2;type=player;view=match |title=Six Nations \u2013 Most drop goals |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=17 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150520235821/http://stats.espnscrum.com/statsguru/rugby/stats/index.html?class=1%3Bfilter%3Dadvanced%3Borderby%3Ddrop_goals%3Btemplate%3Dresults%3Btrophy%3D2%3Btype%3Dplayer%3Bview%3Dmatch |archivedate=20 May 2015 }}\n\n'''Specific'''\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Six nations new}}\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n[[Category:Rugby union records and statistics|Six Nations Hat-trick]]\n[[Category:Six Nations Championship lists|hat-tricks]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:SirCharlesWade.gif|thumb|right|alt=Charles Wade, former England Rugby Union player|[[Charles Wade]], of England, scored the Championship's first hat-trick.]]\nA [[hat-trick]] in [[rugby union]], the scoring of three [[Try (rugby)|tries]] or three [[drop goal]]s in a single match, has been achieved 55 times in the history of the [[Six Nations Championship]]. The annual competition, established in 1882, was originally known as the Home Nations Championship and contested between [[England national rugby union team|England]], [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]], [[Scotland national rugby union team|Scotland]] and [[Wales national rugby union team|Wales]]. It was expanded to the Five Nations when [[France national rugby union team|France]] joined in 1910,{{efn-ua|France were ejected from the competition in 1931 over allegations of professionalism, which was not sanctioned at the time. They were re-admitted in 1939.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/scrum/rugby/story/111894.html |title=Wooller inspires British Army triumph |publisher=ESPN |date=24 February 2010 |accessdate=10 May 2015 |first=Huw |last=Richards }}</ref>}} and then to the Six Nations with the addition of [[Italy national rugby union team|Italy]] in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_union/international/1776391.stm |title=Six Nations history |publisher=BBC Sport |date=28 January 2002 |accessdate=29 April 2016 }}</ref>\n\nThe first player to achieve the feat was [[Charles Wade]], who was an Australian student at [[University of Oxford|Oxford University]] when he was called up as a travelling reserve for England's match against Wales. When [[Philip Newton (rugby player)|Philip Newton]] got lost on his way to the match, Wade was instated in his place.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/england/rugby/story/175962.html |title=England's early great three-quarter |publisher=ESPN |date=22 January 2013 |accessdate=7 May 2016 |first=Huw |last=Richards }}</ref> He scored three tries in England's 2\u20130 victory, which was the first match of the championship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/statsguru/rugby/match/18929.html|title=Wales 0G \u2013 2G England (FT)| publisher= ESPN| accessdate= 6 July 2014}}</ref> At that time, a try by itself was not worth any points but allowed the team to ''try'' and kick a goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.englandrugby.com/twickenham/world-rugby-museum/rugby-history/why-a-try/ |title=Why a try? |publisher=England Rugby |accessdate=10 May 2015 }}</ref> [[George Campbell Lindsay|George Lindsay]] scored five tries in Scotland's 4\u20130 win over Wales in 1887, the most tries scored by a single player in a Championship match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/rugby/fivesix-nations-records-29946477.html |title=Five/Six Nations Records |work=Belfast Telegraph |date=24 January 2014 |accessdate=10 May 2015 }}</ref> \n\nBesides Lindsay, six players have scored more than three tries in a Championship match; of these [[Ian Smith (Scottish rugby player born 1903)|Ian Smith]] is the only player to achieve the feat twice. He scored four tries in successive matches during the [[1925 Five Nations Championship]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/international/scotland/8354953/Six-Nations-2011-Ian-Smiths-record-safe-as-Scotland-try-hard-but-fail-to-cross-line-at-Murrayfield.html |title=Ian Smith's record safe as Scotland try hard but fail to cross line at Murrayfield |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=1 March 2011 |accessdate=18 November 2015 |first=Alasdair |last=Reed }}</ref> Wales' [[Jehoida Hodges]] normally played as a [[Rugby union positions#Forwards|forward]], but after an injury to [[Rugby union positions#Winger|winger]] [[Tom Pearson (rugby player)|Tom Pearson]] during a match against England, Hodges was moved to the [[Rugby union positions#wing|wing]]. Despite playing out of position, he scored a hat-trick in a 21\u20135 victory for Wales.{{sfn|Smith|Williams|1980|p=143}} As of 2017, the only forwards to score a Championship hat-trick while actually playing in the forwards are [[Michel Crauste]]; he scored three tries for France in their 13\u20130 victory over England in [[1962 Five Nations Championship|1962]] and [[C. J. Stander]]; he scored three tries for Ireland in a 63\u201310 win over Italy in [[2017 Six Nations Championship|2017]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/2372660/The-International-Championship-1883-to-2003.html |title=The International Championship 1883 to 2003 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=8 February 2004 |accessdate=7 May 2016 |first=John |last=Griffiths }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rbs6nations.com/en/news/31023.php#uuibB1zhMOMKwPkQ.97|title=VIDEO: Stander and Gilroy make history with hat-tricks|date=11 February 2017|work=rbs6nations.com|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nFour players have scored a hat-trick of drop goals: [[Pierre Albaladejo]], [[Jean-Patrick Lescarboura]], [[Diego Dom\u00ednguez (rugby union)|Diego Dominguez]] and [[Neil Jenkins]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_union/6297867.stm |title=Six nations facts and figures |publisher=BBC Sport |date=25 January 2007 |accessdate=18 November 2015 }}</ref> No Italian has scored a hat-trick of tries in the competition, with Dominguez's hat-trick of drop goals the only one by an Italian player. English players have scored the most hat-tricks with 17, while France, [[Ireland national rugby union team|Ireland]] and Scotland have conceded the most, with 11 each. Three players have scored a hat-trick and been on the losing side; [[Robert Montgomery (rugby union)|Robert Montgomery]] in Ireland's 0\u20131 loss to Wales in 1887,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/statsguru/rugby/match/18955.html |title=Ireland 0G\u20131G Wales |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=11 May 2016 }}</ref> [[Howard Marshall (rugby union)|Howard Marshall]] in England's 11\u201312 defeat to Wales in 1893,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/england/rugby/story/91641.html |title=Elements leave their mark in Cardiff |publisher=ESPN |date=13 February 2009 |accessdate=11 May 2016 }}</ref> and [[\u00c9mile Ntamack]] in France's 33\u201334 loss to Wales in 1999.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/rugby-union-the-day-wales-painted-paris-red-1079185.html |title=The day Wales painted Paris red |work=The Independent |date=8 March 1999 |accessdate=18 November 2015 |first=Tim |last=Glover }}</ref> Lescarboura's hat-trick against England in 1985 and Jenkins' against Scotland in 2001, are the only times the feat has been achieved with the match ending in a draw.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sarugbymag.co.za/blog/details/andrew-rescues-england |title=The day Andrew rescued England |work=SA Rugby Magazine |date=31 January 2014 |accessdate=18 November 2015 |first=Jeremy |last=Proome }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/in_depth/2001/six_nations/1175958.stm |title=Late Scottish surge frustrates Wales |publisher=BBC News |date=17 February 2001 |accessdate=11 May 2016 }}</ref> The most recent hat-trick was achieved by [[Josh Adams (rugby union)|Josh Adams]] against Italy on 1 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-union/51318392 |title=Six Nations 2020: Josh Adams hat-trick helps Wales thrash Italy |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 February 2020 |accessdate=1 February 2020 |first=Gareth |last=Griffiths }}</ref>\n\n== Hat-tricks ==\n[[File:Reggie Gibbs.jpg|thumb|right|alt=Reggie Gibbs|[[Reggie Gibbs]] of Wales scored a hat-trick in both the 1910 and 1911 tournaments.]]\n\n[[File:Brian O'Driscoll 2.jpg|thumb|right|alt=Former Irish rugby union player, Brain O'Driscoll|[[Brian O'Driscoll]] is the only Irishman to have scored two hat-tricks in the tournament's history.]]\n\n[[File:Chris Ashton 2011.jpg|thumb|right|England rugby union player, Chris Ashton|[[Chris Ashton]]'s four tries in 2011 against Italy is the most by one player in a single Championship match since 1969.]]\n\n* All statistics are correct as of 1 February 2020.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\"|Key\n|-\n|-\n!align=\"left\" scope=\"row\"|<sup>4</sup>\n|align=\"left\"|Player scored four tries\n|-\n!align=\"left\" scope=\"row\"|<sup>5</sup>\n|align=\"left\"|Player scored five tries\n|}\n\n===Tries===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+Six Nations Championship try hat-tricks\n! scope=col|No.\n! scope=col|Player\n! scope=col|For\n! scope=col|Against\n! scope=col|Result\n! scope=col|Venue\n! scope=col|Date\n|-\n| 1\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Charles|Wade}}\n| {{ru|ENG}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| align=center|{{sort|02|2\u20130}}\n| [[St. Helen's Rugby and Cricket Ground|St. Helen's]], Swansea\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1882|12|16}}\n|-\n| 2\n!scope=row| {{sortname|George|Lindsay|George Campbell Lindsay}}<sup>5</sup>\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| align=center|{{sort|04|4\u20130}}\n| [[Raeburn Place]], Edinburgh\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1887|2|26}}\n|-\n| 3\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Robert|Montgomery|Robert Montgomery (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| {{ru|WAL}}\n| align=center|{{sort|00|0\u20131}}\n| [[Birkenhead Park]]\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1887|3|12}}\n|-\n| 4\n!scope=row| {{sortname|William|Wotherspoon|William Wotherspoon (rugby union)}}\n| {{ru|SCO}}\n| {{ru|IRE}}\n| align=center|14\u20130\n| Ballynafeigh, Belfast\n| {{dts|format=dmy|1891|2|21}}\n|-\n| 5\n!scope=row| {{sortname|Howard|