 Airlines]] | [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[Louisville International Airport|Louisville]]\n|[[Fedex]] | [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]]\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ '''Top Routes from Las Am\u00e9ricas<br> (2019)'''<ref>[http://www.jac.gob.do/transparencia/index.php/estadisticas/category/521-4to-trimestre {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401200126/http://www.jac.gob.do/transparencia/index.php/estadisticas/category/521-4to-trimestre |date=2019-04-01 }}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! City\n! Passengers\n! Carriers\n|-\n| 1\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York-JFK]]\n| 959,951\n| [[Delta Air Lines]], [[JetBlue]]\n|-\n| 2\n| {{flagicon|US}} [[Miami International Airport|Miami]]\n| 441,987\n| [[American Airlines]]\n|-\n| 3\n| {{flagicon|US}} [[Newark Liberty International Airport|Newark]]\n| 429,160\n| [[United Airlines]], [[Spirit Airlines]]\n|-\n| 4\n| {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Barajas International Airport|Madrid]]\n| 387,576\n| [[Air Europa]], [[Iberia (airline)|Iberia]]\n|-\n| 5\n| {{flagicon|Panama}} [[Tocumen International Airport|Panama City]]\n| 320,322\n| [[Copa Airlines]]\n|-\n| 6\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Fort Lauderdale International Airport|Fort Lauderdale]]\n| 240,830\n| [[JetBlue]], [[Spirit Airlines]]\n|-\n| 7\n| {{flagicon|PRI}} [[Luis Mu\u00f1oz Marin International Airport|San Juan]]\n| 224,242\n| [[JetBlue]]\n|-\n| 8\n| {{flagicon|US}} [[Orlando International Airport|Orlando]]\n| 200,725\n| [[JetBlue]]\n|-\n| 9\n| {{flagicon|US}} [[Logan International Airport|Boston]]\n| 162,231\n| [[JetBlue]]\n|-\n| 10\n| {{flagicon|US}} [[Atlanta International Airport|Atlanta]]\n| 129,653\n| [[Delta Airlines]]\n|-\n| 11\n| {{flagicon|Venezuela}} [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar International Airport (Venezuela)|Caracas]]\n| 118,324\n| [[Avior Airlines]], [[Conviasa]], [[LASER Airlines]], [[Venezolana]]\n|-\n| 12\n| {{flagicon|COL